<font color="#FF0000">SPAM FIX!</font><br>
<tt>Wed Sep 24 23:04:13 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Just had a minor episode tonight over something that was logically not a problem. It did, however, generate a fear which immediately slid into &quot;combat mode&quot; to correct the problem. Some irrational probabilities of action spiraled outward at the same time. I was really going to FIX it! I had to re-establish control over that which had disturbed the universe as I have created it, to be safe.<br><br>
Triggers, threats to my physical and mental safety, spawns fear. <br><br>
Fear releases the demon.<br><br>
The demon goes forth and fixes things.<br><br>
The fixes destroy more than they cure.<br><br>
I am destroyed a little more each time this happens.<br><br>
In the end, I am really fixing nothing but an illusion.<br><br>
This is the price I pay for control of a safe place in which I protect myself from the realities and unresolved conflicts that haunt me.<br><br>
I manage the demon by acknowledging and facing myself, for the demon is truly me.<br><br>
The only reason my demon is so readily available is because I never had closure on my Vietnam experience. The events are as real to me today as they were then. They are above bad memories. I never left. I am still in 'Nam somewhere in my head. I supressed it all to remain safe. I am not safe from myself.<br><br>
I know I am in really bad shape when I cannot remember exactly what I did when the demon is out working the scene.<br><br>
Wicked sucky! No cure, just a lot of hard work. I will always have this. I just don't want to pass it along to someone else. I am sure that dealing with me sometimes could be considered an experience somewhat outside the range of human experience! I really don't like myself when things happen. Backlash realy stings, too.<br><br>
I guess I need the spam fix!<br><br>
Art  
